                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.0031/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-26T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 26, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 26—5:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>277. The Foreign Secretary, when handing me a memorandum on British commercial
                    policy, said that he hoped we would find the statement clear and reasonable and
                    added that he was pleased that the Board of Trade had cooperated to an extent
                    that was gratifying to him.</p>
                <p>The memorandum is six pages in length and is difficult to summarize
                    satisfactorily. Do you wish me to send it by the direct wire or bring it with me
                    on the <hi rend="italic">Queen Mary?</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
